<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?mso-infoPathSolution PIVersion="1.0.0.0" href="file:///C:\ProgramData\Carisbrooke%20Shipping%20Ltd\ISM%20Dashboard\Repository\Forms\Technical%20and%20Safety\RAF%20-%20Risk%20Assessment%20Form%20v2.xsn" name="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:infopath:RAF---Risk-Assessment-Form:-myXSD-2010-09-08T18-23-10" solutionVersion="6.0.0.0" productVersion="14.0.0" ?><?mso-application progid="InfoPath.Document" versionProgid="InfoPath.Document.2"?><my:Main my:DateCreated="" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:od="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:officedata" xmlns:my="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/infopath/2003/myXSD/2010-09-08T18:23:10" xmlns:xd="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/infopath/2003" xml:lang="en-gb"><my:Details><my:Number>G 11</my:Number><my:Title>Manual Handling</my:Title></my:Details><my:Hazards><my:Hazard my:HazardId="1"><my:Description>Personal injury</my:Description><my:Severity>1</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>2</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) All crew must be aware of the correct procedure for manual lifting and carrying; 
b) Look for sharp objects, protruding nails or splinters, for surfaces that are greasy or otherwise difficult to grip or for any other features that may prove awkward or dangerous; 
c) Consult 'Code of Safe Working Practices for Merchant Seamen - Chapter 19'.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>1</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="2"><my:Description>Weight of load</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Use of appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves; 
b) Assess the load to be lifted, taking into account any information that may be provided; 
c) Be aware that the centre of gravity may differ from the geometrical centre of the load; 
d) A trial lift should be carried out and If the load is too heavy for one person, two or more people of similar stature should assist in the handling of the load; 
e) Use any mechanical aids provided i.e. chain blocks, trolleys, sack trucks, etc., to handle the load.</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="3"><my:Description>Slips and trips</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Adequate lighting to be provided. 
b) Ensure that the deck or area over which the load is to be moved is free of any obstructions and not slippery; 
c) The load should be carried so that it does not obscure vision, therefore allowing any obstruction to be seen;</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="4"><my:Description>Environmental factors i.e. confined spaces, temperatures</my:Description><my:Severity>2</my:Severity><my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew to wear suitable PPE to existing temperatures; 
b) Breaks should be taken at regular intervals;</my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="5"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="6"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="7"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="8"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMeasures><my:ReducedSeverity xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedSeverity><my:ReducedLikelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:ReducedLikelihood><my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:ReducedRiskFactor></my:Hazard><my:Hazard my:HazardId="9"><my:Description></my:Description><my:Severity xsi:nil="true"></my:Severity><my:Likelihood xsi:nil="true"></my:Likelihood><my:RiskFactor></my:RiskFactor><my:ControlMeasures></my:ControlMea